Consequences of aversive childhood experiences: effects on the neuroendocrine 
system Abstract. Childhood experiences of stress due to neglect, physical, 
psychological or sexual abuse lead in many cases to permanent changes in the 
stress-regulating neuroendocrine processes. Epidemiological studies already 
